title.narrative: 6.1. By 2021, government and partners have in place an integrated child and family welfare system to prevent and respond to violence, abuse, exploitation and neglect.

description.narrative: Progress to date includes: a) continued strengthening of the case management system with a total to date of 49,478 community cases of which 25,737 cases were dealt with by trained volunteers; b) social welfare workforce strengthening through testing of institutionalised training on case management and alternative care with University of Zambia reaching a total of 49 social welfare officers and subsequent mentoring support; c) development of key policies and plans including Social Welfare Workforce Implementation Plan and National Volunteer Policy and National COVID-19 Social Welfare Plan and d) support to implementing COVID-19 prevention and response plan. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:30/06/2020
